Others: The Minnesota Twins selected the contract of Randy Dobnak and designated Diego Castillo for release or assignment ahead of their season finale against the Baltimore Orioles.
Dobnak made four relief appearances with the Twins earlier this year, recording a 5.87 ERA with seven strikeouts across 7 2/3 innings.

Castillo, who was called up on Saturday and pitched two innings in a 9-2 loss to the Orioles, was with the Twins for three stints this season and made seven appearances, recording a 2.70 ERA and six strikeouts across 10 innings.
